Decide the class on your maven project to be executed via the command line
Right click on the java  class fileGo to Properties  copy the path of the file location
Open the command prompt in your laptop and copy the path but remove the filename at the end
Like this cd C:\Users\nandu\Workspace2-git\ATE-Phase2-Junit\src\test\java\com\app\junitDemo
We also need the path of Junit Jar file on your project. We need to get that path from eclipse project
Right click on mavane depency folder > right click on junit jar and go to properties
Go to java source attachment and copt the path as show below
For me it is:
C:/Users/nandu/.m2/repository/org/junit/jupiter/junit-jupiter-api/5.10.0-M1/junit-jupiter-api-5.10.0-M1-sources.jar
Execute below command on your command line now:
# javac -cp C:/Users/nandu/.m2/repository/org/junit/jupiter/junit-jupiter-api/5.10.0-M1/junit-jupiter-api-5.10.0-M1-sources.jar;. TestAnnotation.java
You will get error, ignore them
# java -cp C:/Users/nandu/.m2/repository/org/junit/jupiter/junit-jupiter-api/5.10.0-M1/junit-jupiter-api-5.10.0-M1-sources.jar TestAnnotation.java
You will get error. Submit the same
